of Prometheus-type plumes near the equator favor asthenosphere heating but do not rule out deep mantle dissipation. Both asthenosphere and deep mantle heating may contribute to Io's surface heat flow. The properties of magma transport through the lithosphere and the planform of mantle convection might exert a control on the surface expression of heating at greater depth. {\textcopyright} 1988.},
