nt. The large heavy element masses of many planets ({\$}{\textgreater}50 M{\_}\backslashoplus{\$}) suggest significant amounts of heavy elements in H/He envelopes, rather than cores, such that metal-enriched giant planet atmospheres should be the rule.},
